d%20guardrails%2C%20and%20a%20Business%20Insider%20investigation%20found%20that%20pop%20stars%20like%20Chris%20Brown%2C%20Lil%20Wayne%2C%20and%20Marshmello%20used%20the%20money%20for%20jets%2C%20bonuses%2C%20and%20a%20birthday%20bash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Joni%20Ernst%20of%20Iowa%2C%20who%20chairs%20the%20Small%20Business%20Committee%20that%20moved%20the%20bill%20forward%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20government%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20after%20the%20people%20that%20truly%20didn't%20deserve%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20saw%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20celebrities%20that%20were%20gaming%20the%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20were%20able%20to%20take%20those%20dollars%20and%20buy%20jets%20and%20throw%20fancy%20parties%20and%20do%20things%20like%20that%20%E2%80%94%20boost%20up%20their%20wardrobe.%20That's%20not%20what%20the%20dollars%20were%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20celebrities%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20on%20didn't%20previously%20reply%20to%20comment%20requests%2C%20except%20for%20Lil%20Wayne%2C%20who%20responded%20to%20a%20reporter's%20questions%20with%20an%20explicit%20sexual%20overture.%20The%20SBA%20has%20defended%20its%20fraud%20controls%20and%20said%20in%20late%202024%20that%20it%20was%20still%20looking%20into%20some%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20has%20recently%20sent%20out%20hundreds%20of%20letters%20to%20SVOG%20grantees%20demanding%20that%20they%20repay%20their%20grants%2C%20according%20to%20people%20in%20the%20entertainment%20industry%2C%20but%20details%20on%20which%20grantees%20were%20targeted%20were%20not%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaggie%20Clemmons%2C%20an%20agency%20representative%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20SBA%20is%20%26quot%3Bcontinuously%20fighting%20to%20claw%20back%20fraudulently-obtained%20COVID%20funds%2C%20including%20within%20the%20SVOG%20program%26quot%3B%20and%20criticized%20%26quot%3Binaction%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20Biden%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Restaurant%20Revitalization%20Fund%2C%20which%20cut%20checks%20of%20up%20to%20%2410%20million%2C%20has%20been%20scrutinized%20by%20auditors.%20Nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20funds%20were%20awarded%20without%20doing%20enough%20to%20verify%20that%20grantees%20were%20eligible%2C%20the%20Small%20Business%20Administration's%20inspector%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oversight.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Freports%2F2024-03%2FSBA-OIG-Report-24-09.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.paymentaccuracy.gov%2Fpayment-accuracy-the-numbers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20improper%20payments%20were%20%26quot%3Blikely%26quot%3B%20in%2053%20out%20of%20122%20restaurant%20awards%20it%20analyzed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20still%20needs%20to%20pass%20the%20Senate%20and%20House%20of%20Representatives%20before%20it%20becomes%20law.%20And%20even%20if%20the%20statute%20of%20limitations%20to%20bring%20charges%20is%20extended%2C%20whether%20prosecutors%20will%20clear%20out%20the%20backlog%20of%20pandemic-fraud%20cases%20is%20an%20open%20question.%20The%20agency's%20inspector%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sba.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-10%2FSBA%2520OIG%2520Report%252025-01.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20SBA%20should%20also%20extend%20the%20time%20period%20for%20which%20grant%20recipients%20hold%20on%20to%20their%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20hope%20would%20be%20that%20given%20the%20priorities%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20that%20somewhere%20in%20that%20mix%2C%20we%20have%20those%20that%20will%20go%20after%20the%20fraudsters%2C%26quot%3B%20Ernst%20said.%20%26quot%3BFraud%20is%20fraud%2C%20and%20our%20taxpayers%20really%20need%20to%20know%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20takes%20it%20seriously.%26quot%3B%