a%20bird%E2%80%99s%20eye%20view.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20wife%2C%20Baljit%20Kaur%2C%20took%20up%20dairy%20farming%20to%20supplement%20the%20family%20income.%20Together%2C%20they%20saved%20and%20slowly%20expanded%20operations%20to%20ten%20acres%2C%20adding%20tomatoes%20and%20other%20seasonal%20crops%20into%20the%20mix.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Davinder%E2%80%99s%20goals%20weren%E2%80%99t%20limited%20to%20daily%20sustenance.%20He%20was%20watching%2C%20learning%2C%20and%20experimenting.%20He%20paid%20attention%20to%20water%20use%2C%20invested%20in%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20and%20studied%20the%20market%20carefully.%20His%20approach%20to%20farming%20was%20never%20passive%3B%20it%20was%20strategic.%20Even%20before%20formal%20training%2C%20he%20believed%20in%20treating%20agriculture%20as%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20turning%20point.%20In%202007%2C%20Davinder%20travelled%20to%20Spain%20and%20Italy%20for%20training%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F470043%2Fabhishek-reddy-left-crore-job-himachal-farm-permaculture-manali%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotected%20cultivation.%3C%2Fa%3E%20What%20he%20saw%20there%20shifted%20his%20worldview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFarmers%20were%20growing%20crops%20in%20extreme%20conditions%20with%20the%20help%20of%20polyhouses%20and%20working%20collectively%20through%20cooperatives.%20They%20bypassed%20middlemen%2C%20focused%20on%20quality%2C%20and%20earned%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20also%20observed%20that%20the%20climatic%20conditions%20in%20Italy%20were%20not%20that%20favourable%20for%20agriculture%20as%20compared%20to%20India%2C%20still%2C%20they%20were%20achieving%20high%20productivity%20from%20their%20fields.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20were%20using%20POLY-HOUSE%20to%20give%20an%20ideal%20atmosphere%20to%20the%20crops%20for%20their%20growth%20and%20development.%20Seeing%20